🧠 Troubleshooting Notes

🔐 SSH Connection Issues

❌ Error:

Permission denied (publickey,gssapi-keyex,gssapi-with-mic)

Cause: Wrong key, bad permissions, or incorrect username.

Fixes:

Make sure your .pem file is in the correct path:

ls -l /c/Users/kirab/Downloads/my-key.pem

Set correct permissions:

chmod 400 /c/Users/kirab/Downloads/my-key.pem

Connect using correct user and IP:

ssh -i "/c/Users/kirab/Downloads/my-key.pem" ubuntu@3.140.197.242

Check your EC2 instance uses Amazon Linux 2 or Ubuntu (use ec2-user or ubuntu accordingly).

🔍 Debug SSH:

ssh -i "/path/to/key.pem" ubuntu@<IP> -v

🌐 Apache Not Showing Website

❌ Error:

Browser times out or page not found.

Fixes:

Ensure Apache is installed:

sudo yum install httpd -y     # Amazon Linux 2
sudo apt update && sudo apt install apache2 -y  # Ubuntu

Start and enable Apache:

sudo systemctl start httpd
sudo systemctl enable httpd

Check if Apache is running:

sudo systemctl status httpd   # or apache2

Test locally:

curl http://localhost

🔒 Security Group Rules

Symptoms: Connection refused or timeout.

Fix:
Make sure your EC2 Security Group allows inbound on:

Port 22 (SSH) from your IP

Port 80 (HTTP) from anywhere (0.0.0.0/0)

🧾 File Upload/Permission Problems

Example: Website not showing updated files.

Fixes:

Use correct permissions:

sudo chown -R ec2-user:ec2-user /var/www/html
chmod -R 755 /var/www/html

Upload via Git or SCP:

git clone https://github.com/Tommy813-lab/aws-ec2-git-bash-demo.git
cp -r ./your-site/* /var/www/html

🌩️ Key Pair Mismatch

Issue: SSH fails despite everything seeming correct.

Root Cause: Key pair used to create the instance doesn't match the .pem file.

Fix:

Terminate instance and relaunch with the correct key pair.

Make sure to keep your .pem file secure.

📦 curl Shows 403 or 404

Fix:

Check file exists in /var/www/html/

Check Apache config (virtual host or index.html present)

Restart Apache:

sudo systemctl restart httpd












